00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.641
Find the Shaded Area

2
00:00:01.641 --> 00:00:03.282
1. Problem

3
00:00:03.282 --> 00:00:07.467
Original image: Find the area of the shaded region.

4
00:00:07.467 --> 00:00:18.873
Meaning: The figure is a right triangle. A shaded rectangle is placed at the lower left, and its upper-right corner lies on the hypotenuse.

5
00:00:18.873 --> 00:00:23.714
The remaining height above the rectangle on the left is 2 .

6
00:00:23.714 --> 00:00:28.309
The remaining base to the right of the rectangle is 10 .

7
00:00:28.309 --> 00:00:31.509
Find: the area of the shaded rectangle.

8
00:00:31.509 --> 00:00:34.955
2. Method 1: Variables + Similar Triangles

9
00:00:34.955 --> 00:00:39.222
Let the shaded rectangle have width x and height y .

10
00:00:39.222 --> 00:00:40.863
Shaded area: S = xy

11
00:00:40.863 --> 00:00:44.227
Total height of the large triangle: y + 2

12
00:00:44.227 --> 00:00:47.510
Total base of the large triangle: x + 10

13
00:00:47.510 --> 00:00:56.125
The small right triangle is similar to the whole large triangle, so corresponding sides are proportional:

14
00:00:56.125 --> 00:00:57.766
Cross multiply:

15
00:00:57.766 --> 00:00:59.407
Expand:

16
00:00:59.407 --> 00:01:01.787
Subtract 10y from both sides:

17
00:01:01.787 --> 00:01:04.659
The shaded area is exactly xy , so:

18
00:01:04.659 --> 00:01:07.039
Shaded area = 20 square units

19
00:01:07.039 --> 00:01:11.059
3. Method 2: Cut-and-Fill, Complete the Rectangle

20
00:01:11.059 --> 00:01:17.131
Completed diagram: The original figure is extended into a large rectangle.

21
00:01:17.131 --> 00:01:22.629
After completing the figure, we get a large rectangle. Notice that:

22
00:01:22.629 --> 00:01:28.701
The height of the added shaded strip on top is the left marked length, 2 .

23
00:01:28.701 --> 00:01:34.855
The length from the middle vertical line to the right bottom corner is 10 .

24
00:01:34.855 --> 00:01:39.532
So the area of the added upper-right shaded rectangle is:

25
00:01:39.532 --> 00:01:49.625
Now look at the slanted line from the upper-left corner to the lower-right corner. It is a diagonal of the large rectangle.

26
00:01:49.625 --> 00:01:54.876
A diagonal of a rectangle divides it into two equal-area parts .

27
00:01:54.876 --> 00:02:05.790
Therefore, the added shaded area above equals the corresponding shaded area below, which is the original lower-left shaded rectangle.

28
00:02:05.790 --> 00:02:08.744
So the original shaded area is also:

29
00:02:08.744 --> 00:02:11.123
Shaded area = 20 square units

30
00:02:11.123 --> 00:02:12.764
4. Summary

31
00:02:12.764 --> 00:02:16.539
There are two good ways to solve this problem:

32
00:02:16.539 --> 00:02:24.498
Similar-triangle method: Use variables for the rectangle and set up a proportion to get xy = 20 .

33
00:02:24.498 --> 00:02:37.134
Cut-and-fill method: Complete the figure into a rectangle and use the fact that a rectangle’s diagonal halves its area, giving the shaded area as 10 × 2 .

34
00:02:37.134 --> 00:02:39.514
Final answer: 20 square units
